OL,4,Charassed women
OL,6,FMr McCrerae said: "She felt she
OL,7,Fcouldn't say no to plans and she
OL,8,Fstarted to feel intimidated and
OL,9,Fscared."
OL,11,FWhen Ms Marlow said she could not
OL,12,Fattend social events, Sutcliffe
OL,13,F"became hostile". He also sent an
OL,14,Fimage of his naked chest.
OL,16,FHe sent further messages throughout
OL,17,FAugust. In September, Sutcliffe went
OL,18,Fto Ms Marlow's home uninvited with
OL,19,Fflowers, a bottle of wine and lollies
OL,20,Ffor her children.
