OL,6,FIn her victim impact statement Ms
OL,7,FMarlow said she continued to feel
OL,8,Femotional on a day-to-day basis and
OL,9,Fthe harassment left her feeling
OL,10,F"vulnerable and living in fear of
OL,11,Fhaving to change routines of myself
OL,12,Fand my family".
OL,14,FShe had CCTV installed at her home and
OL,15,Fbecame nervous.
OL,17,FSutcliffe also targeted his manager,
OL,18,FYorkshire Live's head of news Faye
OL,19,FPreston.
