OL,4,Charassed women
OL,6,FMr McCrerae said: "She said he wanted
OL,7,Fto make her feel vulnerable and
OL,8,Fanxious and 'everything I am not.' She
OL,9,Fsaid she felt his behaviour was
OL,10,Fdegrading and by posting pictures of
OL,11,Fher on Twitter to his hundreds of
OL,12,Ffollowers and colleagues she felt it
OL,13,Fwas demeaning and humiliating".
OL,15,FMs Preston said she was left
OL,16,Fstruggling to eat and sleep and was
OL,17,F"constantly" refreshing Twitter, to
OL,18,Fthe point colleagues and friends
OL,19,Fstepped in to support her.
