OL,3,C'Misogyny' of former journalist who
OL,4,Charassed women
OL,6,FSutcliffe was arrested again and a
OL,7,Fdecision was made to charge him. He
OL,8,Fwent on to plead guilty to five counts
OL,9,Fof harassment without violence.
OL,11,FThe court heard Sutcliffe suffered
OL,12,Fwith depression and bipolar disorder.
OL,14,FMr Sayeris, mitigating, said: "He has
OL,15,Fworked in journalism from 1989 up
OL,16,Funtil his suspension last year. A
OL,17,Fsignificant degree of his identity was
OL,18,Ftied to his job. He has been dogged by
OL,19,Fmental illness throughout his life,
OL,20,Fmade worse by the loss of his
OL,21,Fprofession.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G14/17
